openai was started in 2015 with an ambitious plan to one day create a superintelligent automated system that can do everything a human brain can do.
but friction plagued the companyâs board, which hadnât even been able to agree on replacements for members who had stepped down.

nearly all of openaiâs 800 employees had threatened to follow mr. altman to microsoft, which asked him to lead an a.i. lab with greg brockman, who quit his roles as openaiâs president and board chairman in solidarity with mr. altman.

hours later, he signed a letter with other employees that demanded the independent directors resign.
